This paper is about a neural approach to grammatical error correction, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses pre-training and transfer learning, which are common techniques in machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of a spellchecker, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the release of code and materials for reproducibility, which is related to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
